00:45:19,340 --> 00:45:21,780
So that's 10D6.

1052
00:45:21,780 --> 00:45:22,620
Nice.

1053
00:45:22,620 --> 00:45:24,539
Do you wanna roll that?

1054
00:45:24,539 --> 00:45:25,620
Sure I do.

1055
00:45:25,620 --> 00:45:28,300
35 fall damage.

1056
00:45:28,300 --> 00:45:29,980
Heck yeah. Yeah.

1057
00:45:29,980 --> 00:45:31,500
Okay.

1058
00:45:32,900 --> 00:45:36,380
Describe to me what it looks like.

1059
00:45:36,380 --> 00:45:37,620
The sickening noise.

1060
00:45:37,620 --> 00:45:38,740
The sickening noise.

1061
00:45:38,740 --> 00:45:40,940
With his crack and dies.

1062
00:45:40,940 --> 00:45:45,140
As it hits the bottom of the ocean floor.

1063
00:45:45,140 --> 00:45:48,820
Let's say it starts free falling

1064
00:45:48,820 --> 00:45:50,820
through what is now air.

1065
00:45:50,820 --> 00:45:52,180
And it looks disgusting

1066
00:45:52,180 --> 00:45:56,340
cause it's all like soft and weird and loose.

1067
00:45:56,340 --> 00:45:58,300
It's like lost its form sort of.

1068
00:45:58,300 --> 00:45:59,140
Yeah.

1069
00:45:59,140 --> 00:46:00,100
And then it falls.

1070
00:46:00,100 --> 00:46:03,380
And unfortunately there is a pirate ship

1071
00:46:03,380 --> 00:46:04,860
on the bottom of the ocean

1072
00:46:04,860 --> 00:46:07,340
and it steps right through the mast.

1073
00:46:07,340 --> 00:46:09,820
It falls right down onto it.

1074
00:46:09,820 --> 00:46:10,660
It's a real,

1075
00:46:10,660 --> 00:46:11,500
That is the best.

1076
00:46:11,500 --> 00:46:13,220
This is a real little mermaid situation.

1077
00:46:13,220 --> 00:46:15,380
I like it.

1078
00:46:15,380 --> 00:46:16,220
That's awesome.

1079
00:46:16,220 --> 00:46:17,940
That happens.

1080
00:46:17,940 --> 00:46:19,260
It explodes up.

1081
00:46:19,260 --> 00:46:22,980
And then I presume you drop the spell

1082
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:24,980
as it gets clearer that you die

1083
00:46:24,980 --> 00:46:27,820
and like this water cascades down on top of it.

1084
00:46:27,820 --> 00:46:29,420
You all kind of survey the scene

1085
00:46:29,420 --> 00:46:30,420
and look to each other.

1086
00:46:30,420 --> 00:46:32,539
And then notice that the tethers

1087
00:46:32,539 --> 00:46:35,820
are just moving just within reach.

1088
00:46:35,820 --> 00:46:38,380
And you grab them and zip off behind

1089
00:46:38,380 --> 00:46:41,940
climbing back up into the vessel.

1090
00:46:42,820 --> 00:46:46,340
You get back inside and some time passes.

1091
00:46:46,340 --> 00:46:48,180
How does Sully's story end first of all?

1092
00:46:48,180 --> 00:46:50,539
And we were really surprised to get

1093
00:46:50,539 --> 00:46:55,100
that baby shower invitation in the mail.

1094
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:57,620
We thought she was way past the time when she could,

1095
00:46:57,620 --> 00:46:58,460
but you know what?

1096
00:46:58,460 --> 00:46:59,300
Love is love.

1097
00:46:59,300 --> 00:47:03,500
And hopefully, you know,

1098
00:47:03,500 --> 00:47:05,140
they live happily ever after.

1099
00:47:05,140 --> 00:47:08,300
Cause I mean, we haven't seen them in a while.

1100
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:11,740
It's, wow, that kid would be like eight years old now.

1101
00:47:12,780 --> 00:47:14,019
Damn.

1102
00:47:14,019 --> 00:47:15,820
Time flies, am I right?

1103
00:47:15,820 --> 00:47:19,620
Couple hours have passed and you're all recovering,

1104
00:47:19,620 --> 00:47:22,420
sitting kind of mending your wounds.

1105
00:47:23,300 --> 00:47:24,780
Are we?

1106
00:47:24,780 --> 00:47:27,260
Not completely, not yet.

1107
00:47:27,260 --> 00:47:32,260
And the vessel's going and there's like a disruption.

1108
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:34,860
Like you feel it like,

1109
00:47:34,860 --> 00:47:38,260
like almost like it goes over a heavy speed bump.

1110
00:47:38,260 --> 00:47:39,500
Everybody else feel that?

1111
00:47:40,620 --> 00:47:42,980
Yeah, it's a little bumpy.

1112
00:47:44,539 --> 00:47:45,380
I don't know.

1113
00:47:45,780 --> 00:47:47,700
New territory for me.

1114
00:47:47,700 --> 00:47:50,660
It's feeling, it feels different though.

1115
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:56,700
There's a wash of energy that fills through the vessel.

1116
00:47:59,099 --> 00:48:00,780
And what you don't see,

1117
00:48:00,780 --> 00:48:04,180
but the camera kind of zooms out of the ship

1118
00:48:04,180 --> 00:48:07,019
and up above the ocean is you've passed

1119
00:48:07,019 --> 00:48:08,500
through this barrier.

1120
00:48:08,500 --> 00:48:12,539
And on the other side of this barrier is

1121
00:48:12,579 --> 00:48:17,579
bright sunlight, a green forested island

1122
00:48:18,699 --> 00:48:23,699
and clean, clear, breathable air

1123
00:48:27,219 --> 00:48:30,619
as we look over the island of Maztica.

1124
00:48:43,539 --> 00:48:46,779
It's the end of the week and it's in a quiet space.

1125
00:48:46,779 --> 00:48:48,940
There's a little low murmured conversation

1126
00:48:48,940 --> 00:48:50,659
of Flint and his family,

1127
00:48:50,659 --> 00:48:53,739
but Flint isn't really taking part in it.

1128
00:48:53,739 --> 00:48:58,739
There's a well put together spread for a buffet

1129
00:48:59,539 --> 00:49:04,139
and Flint is seated there deep in thought,

1130
00:49:04,139 --> 00:49:08,820
looking through the crowd, through his family,

1131
00:49:08,820 --> 00:49:10,579
through the conversation,

1132
00:49:10,579 --> 00:49:15,019
just kind of mindlessly picking at the food on his plate.

1133
00:49:15,019 --> 00:49:20,019
And your concentration or lack thereof is broken

1134
00:49:20,139 --> 00:49:22,019
when hell just speaks up and says,

1135
00:49:22,019 --> 00:49:25,659
ah, you feeling all right there, Flint?

1136
00:49:27,340 --> 00:49:29,539
Yeah, it's just, I don't know,

1137
00:49:29,539 --> 00:49:34,019
had this guy in the jail, this Dragonborn the other day,

1138
00:49:34,019 --> 00:49:37,579
and he was talking like just absolute nonsense

1139
00:49:37,579 --> 00:49:42,579
about rivers and chult and somebody named Scyther.

1140
00:49:46,420 --> 00:49:48,500
I don't know, he'd been in jail for like a day and a half,

1141
00:49:48,500 --> 00:49:52,259
but he had this whole other story going on in his head.

1142
00:49:52,259 --> 00:49:54,099
Was he one of the drunk tank ones?

1143
00:49:54,099 --> 00:49:57,099
Like could he have just dreamed it up?

1144
00:49:57,099 --> 00:49:58,980
I mean, maybe, I don't know.

1145
00:49:58,980 --> 00:50:02,579
I asked him if he was one of those dream walkers

1146
00:50:02,579 --> 00:50:05,819
that you've heard about, but he didn't really answer me.

1147
00:50:05,860 --> 00:50:07,580
And then, of course, I had to let him go.

1148
00:50:07,580 --> 00:50:09,300
He paid his fine, so.

1149
00:50:09,300 --> 00:50:10,140
Right.

1150
00:50:10,140 --> 00:50:10,980
But yeah, I don't know.

1151
00:50:10,980 --> 00:50:13,059
It's just, he's just been stuck in my head

1152
00:50:13,059 --> 00:50:14,660
ever since then.

1153
00:50:14,660 --> 00:50:15,820
Did he look familiar?

1154
00:50:15,820 --> 00:50:20,340
Like maybe you knew him from some military days or?

1155
00:50:20,340 --> 00:50:23,380
I don't think so, but something in the back of my mind

1156
00:50:23,380 --> 00:50:25,019
says that he did look familiar,

1157
00:50:25,019 --> 00:50:26,940
but I can't place where he's from.

1158
00:50:28,019 --> 00:50:29,980
Maybe you'll see him around and you can ask him.

1159
00:50:29,980 --> 00:50:31,539
You know what, maybe I will.

1160
00:50:31,539 --> 00:50:33,580
I don't think he's gonna stick around town, though.

1161
00:50:33,579 --> 00:50:36,059
I don't think he had a great time here.

1162
00:50:36,059 --> 00:50:37,099
Yeah, no, that's fair.

1163
00:50:37,099 --> 00:50:39,019
Or maybe he had too great of a time

1164
00:50:39,019 --> 00:50:42,139
and then doesn't want to revisit that.

1165
00:50:42,139 --> 00:50:44,579
Yeah, that's something.

1166
00:50:44,579 --> 00:50:48,860
Hey, everything else going okay?

1167
00:50:48,860 --> 00:50:50,259
Worked good?

1168
00:50:50,259 --> 00:50:53,819
Yeah, I mean, no major complaints there.

1169
00:50:53,819 --> 00:50:55,759
Glory Gems, good right-hand man.

1170
00:50:56,659 --> 00:51:00,139
Really made some positive changes with the city guard.

1171
00:51:00,139 --> 00:51:02,460
I'm feeling pretty good about where we're at.

1172
00:51:02,500 --> 00:51:03,740
Hear your father's voice.

1173
00:51:03,740 --> 00:51:07,659
Say, past the potatoes there.

1174
00:51:07,659 --> 00:51:11,179
Reaches his hand over and as you look over his hand,

1175
00:51:12,220 --> 00:51:15,780
it gives you a start because his hand is decayed.

1176
00:51:17,940 --> 00:51:21,059
And as you kind of pull back, it snaps back

1177
00:51:21,059 --> 00:51:23,340
and he's there and he looks startled.

1178
00:51:23,340 --> 00:51:26,079
Like, is everything okay?

1179
00:51:26,980 --> 00:51:29,300
Yeah, sorry, just, I don't know.

1180
00:51:29,300 --> 00:51:31,440
I had a little,

1181
00:51:32,659 --> 00:51:35,860
a little trick on the old eyes there.

1182
00:51:35,860 --> 00:51:38,099
Here's the potatoes, sorry, there you go.

1183
00:51:38,099 --> 00:51:39,940
Oh, yeah, no, it's okay.

1184
00:51:39,940 --> 00:51:42,539
I guess I just didn't sleep well last night or something.

1185
00:51:42,539 --> 00:51:43,900
Yeah, that's just what I was gonna say.

1186
00:51:43,900 --> 00:51:45,539
Get some more sleep.

1187
00:51:45,539 --> 00:51:47,539
Don't worry about coming in tomorrow.

1188
00:51:47,539 --> 00:51:48,740
We got your shift covered for you.

1189
00:51:48,740 --> 00:51:50,340
Well, I mean, you know I love it,

1190
00:51:50,340 --> 00:51:52,139
but yeah, I might need the day off,

1191
00:51:52,139 --> 00:51:52,980
but we'll see.

1192
00:51:52,980 --> 00:51:56,579
If I have a good night, I'll head in

1193
00:51:56,579 --> 00:52:00,420
and if not, well then, yeah, maybe I'll sit that one out.

1194
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:06,260
Do you have another there, champ?

1195
00:52:06,260 --> 00:52:09,900
Sorry, yeah, yeah, one more.

1196
00:52:09,900 --> 00:52:11,579
One more might be good.

1197
00:52:11,579 --> 00:52:13,980
Same as last time or do you want to mix it up?

1198
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:16,740
Surprise me.

1199
00:52:16,740 --> 00:52:19,220
Okay, I love a challenge.

1200
00:52:19,220 --> 00:52:21,780
The bartender kind of turns around

1201
00:52:21,780 --> 00:52:25,340
and surveys the bottles to choose from

1202
00:52:25,340 --> 00:52:28,300
and grabs one on the right hand side

1203
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:33,300
and it's kind of this orangey, earthy tone kind of bottle

1204
00:52:34,060 --> 00:52:38,900
and he pours two fingers into a glass for ya.

1205
00:52:38,900 --> 00:52:40,500
Says, give that one a try.

1206
00:52:40,500 --> 00:52:41,700
You might like it.

1207
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,140
Port picks it up and holds it up

1208
00:52:43,140 --> 00:52:46,019
to the soft candlelight in this tavern

1209
00:52:46,019 --> 00:52:50,980
and says, all right, downs it.

1210
00:52:50,980 --> 00:52:55,100
And it's a real harsh fiery liquid.

1211
00:52:55,100 --> 00:52:57,060
It hits the back of his throat

1212
00:52:57,099 --> 00:52:59,980
and he kind of winces a little bit and closes his eyes

1213
00:53:00,980 --> 00:53:04,179
and as he opens them, he sees the mirror

1214
00:53:04,179 --> 00:53:08,500
in behind the bartender, like the glass back there

1215
00:53:08,500 --> 00:53:11,420
and looking back at him, just for a split second,

1216
00:53:12,820 --> 00:53:15,019
is that dwarf from the jail?

1217
00:53:15,019 --> 00:53:17,900
He, almost like spit takes,

1218
00:53:17,900 --> 00:53:19,619
but instead of spit coming out,

1219
00:53:19,619 --> 00:53:22,900
like this electricity shoots from his nostrils

1220
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:26,340
and hits the tabletop which starts just a little fire

1221
00:53:26,340 --> 00:53:28,980
that he quickly pats out and says, sorry, sorry, sorry.

1222
00:53:28,980 --> 00:53:31,180
What's up there, dragon man?

1223
00:53:31,180 --> 00:53:33,260
Bad reaction to the booze?

1224
00:53:34,180 --> 00:53:37,700
Yeah, no, sometimes electricity and liquids

1225
00:53:37,700 --> 00:53:39,300
don't go well together.

1226
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:41,860
Hey, is everything okay?

1227
00:53:41,860 --> 00:53:46,860
I think I've been an upstanding citizen today.

1228
00:53:47,220 --> 00:53:48,980
I mean, you've been all right since you've been here.

1229
00:53:48,980 --> 00:53:52,460
Yeah, what brings you to this end of town?

1230
00:53:52,460 --> 00:53:53,620
Just been thinking.

1231
00:53:54,619 --> 00:53:56,019
Mostly about you.

1232
00:53:56,019 --> 00:53:58,299
I'm flattered, I'm flattered, friend.

1233
00:53:58,299 --> 00:54:03,299
Yeah, no, I, something about our meeting stood out.

1234
00:54:04,739 --> 00:54:06,739
I can't get it out of my head.

1235
00:54:06,739 --> 00:54:08,420
Where do I know you from?

1236
00:54:08,420 --> 00:54:09,940
I know you from somewhere.

1237
00:54:11,699 --> 00:54:13,980
You've been around, you've been around Chult?

1238
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:15,659
No, it wasn't Chult.

1239
00:54:15,659 --> 00:54:17,019
No, no.

1240
00:54:17,019 --> 00:54:22,019
You done any time, done any time,

1241
00:54:22,019 --> 00:54:24,500
any time you left the mountain?

1242
00:54:24,500 --> 00:54:27,059
Yeah, I used to be a soldier, but I don't know,

1243
00:54:27,059 --> 00:54:31,619
I just, I remember most dragonborn I've ever met

1244
00:54:31,619 --> 00:54:33,099
few and far between for a dwarf,

1245
00:54:33,099 --> 00:54:36,420
but I just, you're on the tip of my tongue,

1246
00:54:36,420 --> 00:54:38,219
I just can't place you.

1247
00:54:38,219 --> 00:54:40,219
Ever been to the library of the dead?

1248
00:54:41,420 --> 00:54:42,820
Holy shit.

1249
00:54:43,820 --> 00:54:44,659
What?

1250
00:54:44,659 --> 00:54:45,480
It's you.

1251
00:54:47,259 --> 00:54:49,699
Yeah, in the flesh.

1252
00:54:49,699 --> 00:54:51,179
What the fuck is happening?

1253
00:54:53,019 --> 00:54:56,699
I don't know, Flint, how do we get out of here?

1254
00:54:58,019 --> 00:55:00,059
First off, where are we?

1255
00:55:00,059 --> 00:55:04,300
Is this, this, I mean, this isn't right.

1256
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:07,340
It's a perfect world, isn't it?

1257
00:55:07,340 --> 00:55:09,219
Yeah, it's a little too good.

1258
00:55:09,219 --> 00:55:13,820
Yeah, well, for some, mine's been a hellscape

1259
00:55:13,820 --> 00:55:16,739
of constant running, trying to find a way out,

1260
00:55:16,739 --> 00:55:18,940
and now I'm back to you.

1261
00:55:18,940 --> 00:55:21,099
You made that choice, though.

1262
00:55:21,099 --> 00:55:21,940
Yeah.

1263
00:55:23,579 --> 00:55:27,339
Didn't make a choice to be soulbound.

1264
00:55:27,339 --> 00:55:30,099
Okay, okay, yeah, you didn't make that choice,

1265
00:55:30,099 --> 00:55:31,779
but you made the choice to run.

1266
00:55:32,819 --> 00:55:35,259
Yeah, yeah, I did.

1267
00:55:35,259 --> 00:55:38,619
I mean, could it, I really could have used your help

1268
00:55:38,619 --> 00:55:42,460
at the Well of the Dragons, and I get why you didn't,

1269
00:55:42,460 --> 00:55:44,819
but like, things could have turned out

1270
00:55:44,819 --> 00:55:46,460
a whole lot differently.

1271
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,460
I tried to make it so that you

1272
00:55:48,460 --> 00:55:50,500
could just be you, Flint.

1273
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:55,500
But it doesn't look like the universe,

1274
00:55:55,500 --> 00:56:00,019
or the gods, or whoever wants that to happen.

1275
00:56:01,380 --> 00:56:03,539
Yeah, it's been a bit of an uphill battle.

1276
00:56:05,980 --> 00:56:07,019
So what's next?

1277
